AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!! Meet Rudy one of the most amazing dogs you will ever meet! This handsome petite Lab/Terrier mix was born around July 2017. The one word everyone uses to describe him is SWEET! This easy going and social boy was recently rescued from an area shelter after being hit by a car. He had an injury to his back leg that could not be saved and he had to have it amputated. If there was ever a dog that could teach us all what it means to be survivor, it is Rudy. He has not missed beat and is running and playing on all three legs like a puppy should. He is in a foster home with children and other dogs and doing great. He loves his chew toys. On most days you will find him outside in the fenced yard running and playing with his fosterâ€™s dogs. After a long day of play, he loves to snuggle right up next to you. He is doing great with house and crate training and rides well in the car. He is a super smart boy that is eager to please. He currently weighs 20lbs and will weigh around 30lbs full grown. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines and microchipped. If you are looking for a truly awesome dog, then Rudy is the boy for you. ADOPT WOODSTOCK & PEANUT ğŸ˜»ğŸ˜½
We are accepting applications for our beautiful 4 mos old kitten pair Woodstock and Peanut! Our goal is to keep this brother and sister together forever. They both arrived to us as little teeny feral kitties and they have come a long way since then. They have tested negative for FIV and FeLV. They are being treated for worms and hopefully should be clear next test. They were neutered and spayed (poor Peanut's uterus was attached to her bladder ğŸ˜± and it was successfully separated.) Woodstock aka Woody is our boy and he's a sweet little mush who was scared at first and quickly transformed into a super little all around friendly cat!
Peanut, our girl, is a work in progress and needs a loving, patient, cat experienced family to continue to love and socialize her. Initially she would hide but now she hangs out and we call that progress. She's still not thrilled about a lot of handling and will probably never be a lap cat but who knows! They are companions though and we would love to keep them together. If you are interested in these babies contact us at getabullrescue@gmail.com
